 systems. This would also resolve the apparent\ncontradiction with the precession of the neutron stars. We also discuss some\ninstances where anomalous induced current may play a crucial role, such as the\nneutron star kicks, pulsar glitches and the toroidal magnetic field.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Jan 2007 18:15:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 10 Jan 2007 21:15:00 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Wed, 31 Jan 2007 02:39:27 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-11-26"}
